cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper discusses textureless object recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the application of textureless object recognition in robotics and manufacturing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning techniques indicates that it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the mention of the International Conference on Smart Multimedia suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
